cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the problem of human pose estimation in real-world videos of swimmers using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the modifications made to the architecture to leverage activity information and the continuous nature of the video recordings, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of the recordings for performance analysis of athletes, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the manual annotations of body parts in each video frame, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper discusses the error modes of the baseline architecture, which could be categorized under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
